8 An Act relating to career technology; creating Career
Technology Business Partnership Pool; providing for
9 exclusive use of pool amounts; providing for issuance
of obligations; authorizing issuance of tax-exempt
10 obligations; requiring financial literacy curriculum;
prohibiting certain indebtedness; providing for
11 termination of program; amending 62 O.S. 2021,
Sections 891.3 and 891.15, which relate to the
12 Oklahoma Community Economic Development Pooled
Finance Act; modifying definitions; modifying
13 references; providing for codification; and providing
an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 891.8A of Title 62, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Authority shall be authorized to act as a conduit issuer
21 for the benefit of one or more career technology districts in
22 conjunction with one or more for-profit business entities for an
23 authorized economic development project using the Career Technology
24 Business Partnership Pool.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3429 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. The Authority shall be authorized to issue its obligations
2 in order to provide net proceeds on a pooled basis not to exceed
3 Fifty Million Dollars ($50,000,000.00) for the Career Technology
4 Business Partnership Pool. The Authority shall be authorized to
5 issue obligations within the limit prescribed by this subsection
6 based upon the defeasance of previously issued obligations.
7 C. Proceeds from the Career Technology Partnership Pool shall
8 be for the purpose of providing financing for one or more eligible
9 career technology districts in partnership with one or more for-
10 profit business entities for an authorized economic development
11 project located in this state.
12 D. Obligations issued pursuant to the provisions of this
13 section may be issued on a tax-exempt basis if the applicable
14 provisions of federal law governing private activity bonds allow
15 such issuance. Otherwise, the obligations issued pursuant to the
16 provisions of this section shall be issued on a taxable basis.
17 E. Any career technology district that utilizes the provisions
18 of this act shall have financial literacy as part of its course
19 offerings.
20 F. A career technology district that utilizes the provisions of
21 this act shall not have any outstanding indebtedness at any time
22 during which the district is participating in or otherwise
23 benefitting from the provisions of this act.
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3429 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 G. No career technology district may utilize the provisions of
2 this act after June 30, 2032.
3 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 62 O.S. 2021, Section 891.3, is
4 amended to read as follows:
5 Section 891.3. 1. "Authority" means the Oklahoma Development
6 Finance Authority;
7 2. "Bonds" means any form of obligation issued by the Oklahoma
8 Development Finance Authority pursuant to the Oklahoma Community
9 Economic Development Pooled Finance Act;
10 3. "Business entity" means a corporation, limited liability
11 company, general partnership, limited partnership or such other
12 entity conducting a lawful activity which is organized pursuant to
13 the laws of the state or which is authorized to do business in the
14 state if organized under the law of another jurisdiction;
15 4. "Career Technology Business Partnership Pool" means the
16 proceeds of obligations sold by the Authority to provide resources
17 for one or more eligible career technology districts in partnership
18 with one or more for-profit business entities to finance an eligible
19 economic development project or other purposes authorized by the
20 Oklahoma Community Economic Development Pooled Finance Act;
21 5. "Community Economic Development Pooled Finance Revolving
22 Fund" means the fund created pursuant to Section 891.15 of this
23 title;
24
