(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 5. 6. "Conduit issuer" means the Oklahoma Development Finance
2 Authority acting for the benefit of either a combination of local
3 government entities or a local government entity or entities in
4 conjunction with a for-profit business entity pursuant to the
5 provisions of the Oklahoma Community Economic Development Pooled
6 Finance Act;
7 6. 7. "Credit Enhancement Reserve Fund" means that fund created
8 pursuant to Section 5063.3 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
9 7. 8. "Debt" means bonds, notes or other evidence of
10 indebtedness issued by the Oklahoma Development Finance Authority;
11 8. 9. "Department" means the Oklahoma Department of Commerce;
12 9. 10. "Economic Development Pool" means proceeds of
13 obligations sold by the Authority to provide resources for eligible
14 local government entities or a local government entity in
15 conjunction with a for-profit business entity to finance an eligible
16 economic development project or other purposes authorized by the
17 Oklahoma Community Economic Development Pooled Finance Act;
18 10. 11. "Eligible local government entity" means:
19 a. a city,
20 b. a town,
21 c. a county,
22 d. any combination of cities, towns or counties,
23 e. a public trust with a beneficiary or beneficiary which
24 is a city, town, county or some combination of such
